# 1. Introduction

The **Clinical TFL Viewer v2** is an interactive R Shiny web application designed
for clinical programmers, biostatisticians, and data reviewers. It provides a
unified workspace for viewing, filtering, and investigating Tables, Figures, and
Listings (TFLs) derived from CDISC ADaM analysis datasets.

## 1.1 Purpose

During study conduct and submission preparation, TFLs are produced by R (or SAS)
scripts that read from ADaM datasets. Reviewing these outputs often requires:

- Switching between a formatted table and the underlying data
- Understanding which subjects were included (population flags)
- Exploring whether a specific patient drove a signal
- Reproducing a filtered subset for ad hoc questions

The TFL Viewer v2 makes all of these tasks available without leaving the browser.

## 1.2 Scope of This Document

This guide covers:

- Installation and first launch
- How the app discovers and runs TFL scripts
- A walkthrough of each application tab
- Instructions for adding new TFLs
- Known limitations and the roadmap for improvement

