# 3. Application Architecture

## 3.1 Startup Sequence

```
global.R ──► Generates ADaM data (or loads from SAS/Parquet)
         ──► Sources R/data_gen.R, R/runner.R, R/utils.R
         ──► Calls discover_tfls("tfls/") → tfl_list
         ──► Calls build_registry(tfl_list) → tfl_registry
ui.R     ──► Defines the page layout (runs once)
server.R ──► Reactive session logic (runs once per user)
```

`global.R` executes **once per R worker process**, so data generation and TFL
execution costs are shared across all concurrent users.

## 3.2 TFL Script Convention

Each file in `tfls/` named `tfl_*.R` is treated as a TFL script. The runner
executes it in an isolated child environment that already contains the four ADaM
datasets (`adsl`, `adae`, `adlb`, `adtte`). Scripts must define four objects:

| Object | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `tfl_metadata` | named list | Identity (id, name, type, datasets, description) |
| `source_datasets` | named list | Data frames read by this TFL |
| `filter_code` | character | Filter recipe (shown in the Filter Code tab) |
| `tfl_output` | data.frame or ggplot | The final rendered output |

## 3.3 Reactive Data Flow

```
User selects TFL
    │
    ▼
current_tfl()  ──► TFL Output tab (pre-computed output)
    │               TFL Code tab   (script source)
    │               Filter Code tab (static recipe)
    │
    ▼
raw_dataset()   (one of the TFL's source_datasets)
    │
    ▼ (population flag filters applied)
pop_filtered()  ──► Dataset Explorer → Data sub-tab
                ──► Investigate tab (unique values, patient listing, plot)
                ──► Quick stats in sidebar
                ──► Download handler
                ──► Live filter code
```

