# 6. Connecting to Real Study Data

Replace the `generate_adam_data()` call in `global.R`:

```r
# SAS datasets
library(haven)
adsl  <- read_sas("/path/to/adam/adsl.sas7bdat")
adae  <- read_sas("/path/to/adam/adae.sas7bdat")
adlb  <- read_sas("/path/to/adam/adlb.sas7bdat")
adtte <- read_sas("/path/to/adam/adtte.sas7bdat")
adam  <- list(adsl = adsl, adae = adae, adlb = adlb, adtte = adtte)
```

Column names in the TFL scripts follow CDISC ADaM conventions. If your datasets
use different names, update the scripts accordingly.

