# 7. What Works Well

- **Zero-configuration TFL registration** – drop a script in `tfls/`, click Refresh
- **Graceful failure handling** – a broken script is flagged ❌ in the registry; the rest of the app continues normally
- **Population flag auto-detection** – no configuration required; any `*FL` column becomes an interactive filter
- **Live code generation** – the Filter Code tab always shows the exact dplyr code matching current selections
- **Mixed output types** – the same `tfl_output` contract handles both tables and figures transparently
- **Re-run capability** – filtered populations can be passed back into TFL scripts for sensitivity analyses
- **Isolation** – TFL scripts cannot contaminate each other's environments

