# 8. Known Limitations and Improvement Roadmap

## 8.1 High Priority

| # | Issue | Suggested Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Re-run applies population flags only; DT column filters are not captured | Unify flag + column filters into a single reactive filter state |
| 2 | `forcats` not listed in `global.R` library() calls | Add `library(forcats)` to `global.R` |
| 3 | Population flag selections reset when switching TFLs | Add `enableBookmarking("url")` + `setBookmarkExclude()` |
| 4 | Column filter quick stats mismatch | Wire DT `state` callback to a reactive to capture column filter values |

## 8.2 Medium Priority

| # | Issue | Suggested Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 5 | Tables are raw data frames, not publication-formatted | Integrate `gt` or `flextable` for spanning headers and footnotes |
| 6 | KM figure has no number-at-risk table | Add `ggsurvfit::add_risktable()` below the x-axis |
| 7 | No figure download button | Add `downloadHandler` with `ggplot2::ggsave()` |
| 8 | Population flags are single-select | Replace `selectInput` with `selectizeInput(multiple = TRUE)` |
| 9 | No authentication | Add `shinymanager` or deploy behind Posit Connect auth |

## 8.3 Low Priority / Future Enhancements

| # | Enhancement |
|---|---|
| 10 | Listing TFL type with pagination-optimised DT options |
| 11 | Parallel TFL execution at startup for large study programmes |
| 12 | Loading spinner / progress bar during `global.R` startup |
| 13 | Configurable study metadata banner (title, sponsor, data cut) |
| 14 | `testthat` unit tests for `data_gen.R`, `runner.R`, and `utils.R` |
| 15 | Quarto-based PDF export of the formatted TFL with study headers/footers |
| 16 | Multi-study support (study selector that swaps the `adam` list) |

